      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "SALT LAKE, May 26.--In the con-\nvention of the Western Federation of\nMiners today members of the execu-\ntive committee were named as dele\ngates to the Chicago convention of\nindustrial unions, June 81, with full\npower to act and become a working\npower in the new movement. Organ\nizer Kennison reported on the condi-\nton in Michigan copper and lead dis\ntricts. He declares skilled miners,\ncarpenters and blacksmiths are re-\nceiving only $3.50 per day of IL\nhours."
    }
